Lula Says IMF Won’t Solve Portugal’s Problem, Radio TSF Reports

-- B y   J o a o   L i m a
-- 
2011-03-29T06:55:56Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-29/lula-says-imf-won-t-solve-portugal-s-problem-radio-tsf-reports.html
Former Brazilian President  Luiz
Inacio Lula da Silva  said an International Monetary Fund
intervention would not solve  Portugal ’s problem, news radio TSF
reported on its website.  “The IMF does not solve Portugal’s problem, just as it did
not solve  Brazil ’s problem,” Lula told reporters in Lisbon last
night, according to TSF. “It created more problems than
solutions.”  Click here for web link  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
